  "title": "Stained Wood Mod",
  "description": "Adds stained variants to wood using craftable vinegar",
  "body": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">With this mod you are able to craft vinegar to stain wood planks. You can also combine any dye with oak planks to create dyed planks.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif; font-size: 24px;\">Crafting Recipes</span></p>\n<div class=\"spoiler\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">(Note: These recipes are shapeless)</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Vinegar</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/2TqjVvW.png\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Stained Planks (all types)</span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/jf2AEnu.png\" width=\"305\" height=\"135\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Dyed planks are created by adding one dye to one oak plank in the crafting menu.</span></p>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Planned Features</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Stained Logs</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">New Compatibilities (Suggestions wanted)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif; font-size: 24px;\">Any Bugs?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">Please tell me! This is my first, simplest mod but many things can still go wrong.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'book antiqua', palatino, serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">The Fabric Version of This Mod Requires Fabric API!</span></strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">Modpack&nbsp;Usage</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: georgia, palatino, serif;\">Feel free to use this mod in a modpack. It's not like it's actually a big mod.</span></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
